SPECIES: common name: RETINAL CELL TYPE NAME: as published
OTHER MOSAICS in same sampling field

Treefrog: Shamim, Tóth, Becker, Cook (1999) Vis Neurosci 16: 861-879

alpha1-ab cells share many features with alpha-a cells in other frogs but are unusual in having dendrites also in sublamina b; alpha2-ab cells share key features with alpha-ab cells in other frogs and do not respect the dendritic territories of alpha1-ab cells although the somata of the two types show 'steric hindrance'
